column3: str

<UIForeground>F201FC</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FD</UIGlow> Quest Sync<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground>
Lonuhali requires a swift pair of legs for an urgent delivery.
Distribute the reed dumplings.
Speak with Lonuhali.
Welcome, honored visitor! Thanks to your efforts, the reeds grow robust, and at last I can make reed dumplings again. Oh, they're every bit as delicious as I remember!

Although I want nothing more than to eat until my belly bursts, I've saved a batch for those who are planning the reconstruction of the great stairs. I'm much too full to make such a journey, however─might you deliver them in my stead?
Surely my friends will be glad to receive them from the very <If(PlayerParameter(4))>woman<Else/>man</If> who revitalized Ok'hanu's festive spirit!
Thank you, thank you! They can be found working hard near the Flight of We Wingless. Hurry before the dumplings cool!
The dumplings are cooling as we speak─hurry and take them to my friends at the Flight of We Wingless!
Oh, I recognize you─you travel with Wuk Lamat, yes? Have you come to see our progress on the great stairs?
Dumplings!? Oh, how long has it been since I last smelled that heavenly aroma...?
When the reeds sprouted big and tall, we had cause to celebrate often, and it was a common scent in Ok'hanu. To have these delivered by one who helped those days to return is a great honor indeed!
This project will cause my feathers to fall out one by one, mark my words... Where do we even begin?
Lonuhali made her famous dumplings!? These are just what I needed...such a large undertaking makes one so very hungry!

With my energies restored, I've come to a realization. Our reed problem required the perspective of visitors to solve, so perhaps we should consult artisans from other clans for advice on how to repair the great stairs.
Ohokaliy! Apologies, but this area is still impassable.
You brought reed dumplings!? Just as I was about to keel over from hunger, a kind soul appears from the wilderness to save me!
This passage is of great importance to us, since no small number of merchants use it to reach Ok'hanu. With delicious dumplings to fuel me, I can now tackle this problem with renewed energy!
It's been too long since there were enough extra reeds to make dumplings. Thank you for reminding me that better times are upon us!
Your gift has blessed me with a fresh idea. This may be the first step towards finally repairing the great stairs.

While this area can be reached by water routes, the stairs are a much less strenuous journey for all involved. With hunger no longer a distraction, I hope I can finally solve the problem of their reconstruction.
Thank you for delivering the dumplings! I hope they give my friends the energy to complete the daunting task ahead of them.

Reed dumplings are considered delicacy among the Hanuhanu, and for good reason. I would like nothing more than to make a batch for our other wingless brethren who aid with the rebuilding, but I realize that not all peoples love their flavor as much as we do...
But that doesn't mean I can't send a different gift to show my appreciation. I intend to send a nice haul of fish their way!
You don't seem the type to munch on reeds, either, so I've prepared something else for your reward─cold, hard coin!
